>\n\n\n\n<p>III.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>&#8220;Some people get addicted to chain-smoking their problems. They spend all day going from sorrow to sorrow. It doesn&#8217;t have to be that way. You can live each day going from joy to joy\u2014like a sunflower that turns to face the sun as it moves across the sky. It&#8217;s not about having a problem-free life, but about focusing on the light. Sunflowers still have shadows, but they are always behind them.&#8221;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"h-2-quotes-from-others\">2 QUOTES FROM OTHERS<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>I.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Computer scientist and technology blogger <strong>John Gruber<\/strong> on quality:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>&#8220;The quality of any creative endeavor tends to approach the level of taste of whoever is in charge.&#8221;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><em>Source: <\/em><a href=\"https:\/\/www.youtube.com\/watch?v=xk3UcgbbmxQ\">\u200b<em>The Auteur Theory of Design<\/em>\u200b<\/a><em>\u200b (2009)<\/em><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>\u200bII.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Writer and Nobel Prize winner <strong>Gabriel Garc\u00eda M\u00e1rquez<\/strong> on what matters in life:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>&#8220;What matters in life is not what happens to you but what you remember and how you remember it.&#8221;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><em>Source: Interview with Gerald Martin<\/em><\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"h-1-question-for-you\">1 QUESTION FOR YOU<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Imagine your life as a book. What title would you give to the current chapter, and what is going to be the next?<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><em>(<\/em><a href=\"https:\/\/twitter.com\/JardBlo\/status\/1766881990786109801\">\u200b<em>Thanks to Jard<\/em>\u200b<\/a><em> for today&#8217;s question.)<\/em><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><\/p>\n\n\n<div id=\"block_227a964a7f433e412668855365d2c0eb\" class=\"twitter-share \" data-easygut-id=\"twitter\">\n\t<div><a href=\"https:\/\/ctt.ac\/f41c3\"><svg width=\"24\" height=\"27\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 27\" fill=\"none\" xmlns=\"http:\/\/www.w3.org\/2000\/svg\">\n<circle cx=\"12\" cy=\"14\" r=\"12\" fill=\"#EDEADE\"\/>\n<path d=\"M16